						               													<description>Cooperative game. Scour the neighborhood to find what each project calls for before time runs out. The challenges will be proposing different complexities. The ticking clock will be a very important factor to add excitement and fun!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Olivia and Cukito's adventure is the ninth title that we have produced from El Espejo, and it is of great importance to us as it is our first specifically cooperative proposal. It is an invitation to the game for early childhood, with a neighborhood theme where we seek to work on the issue of waste, trying to problematize the idea of &amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#139;&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#139;&amp;quot;individual environmentalism&amp;quot; (see section), emphasizing the importance of cooperative work and proposing as a challenge build works or &amp;quot;manufacturable&amp;quot; objects from said waste. With the premise of promoting group work, throughout the game the challenges intensify in difficulty and in the forms of communication between the players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Olivia, along with Cukito and her friends, are thinking about what to do with so much waste that is scattered around their neighborhood. It occurred to them to put together Projects to recycle, turning some waste into useful objects or reusing them in different ways. To achieve this, they must move at full speed, locker by locker, lifting those elements that serve to complete the projects.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
